<%# JSON-LD schemas %>
<%= breadcrumb_schema([
  { name: "Home", url: root_url },
  { name: "Business Startup Suite", url: suite_business_startup_url }
]) %>

<%= faq_schema([
  { question: "What is a business startup calculator suite?", answer: "A business startup calculator suite is a guided workflow that walks you through the essential financial calculations for launching a business. It covers break-even analysis, loan planning, and return on investment in a logical sequence so each step informs the next." },
  { question: "What should I calculate first when starting a business?", answer: "Start with a break-even analysis. Understanding how many units you need to sell or how much revenue you need to generate to cover your costs is the most fundamental question for any new business. This informs all other financial planning." },
  { question: "How do I know if I need a business loan?", answer: "After completing your break-even analysis, compare the startup costs and operating expenses to your available capital. If you need more money to reach break-even than you have on hand, a business loan can bridge the gap. The Business Loan Calculator helps you understand the true cost of borrowing." },
  { question: "What is a good ROI for a startup?", answer: "A good ROI varies by industry, but most investors look for at least 15-25% annual return on a startup investment. The ROI Calculator helps you project returns based on your expected revenues and costs so you can evaluate whether the business opportunity is worth pursuing." }
]) %>

<%# Breadcrumbs %>
<%= render "shared/breadcrumbs", items: [
  { name: "Home", url: root_path },
  { name: "Business Startup Suite" }
] %>

<div class="mb-10">
  <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4">Business Startup Calculator Suite</h1>
  <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 max-w-3xl">Plan your business finances from the ground up. Work through break-even analysis, loan planning, and ROI projections in a logical order.</p>
</div>

<%= render "shared/ad_slot", slot: "leaderboard" %>

<div class="mt-8 space-y-6" data-controller="suite-stepper">
  <%# Step 1: Break-Even %>
  <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-2xl border border-gray-200/80 dark:border-gray-800 overflow-hidden">
    <button data-action="click->suite-stepper#toggle" class="w-full flex items-center justify-between p-6 text-left group">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
        <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-500 to-orange-600 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold text-lg">1</div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white group-hover:text-amber-600 dark:group-hover:text-amber-400 transition-colors">Break-Even Analysis</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-1">Find out how much revenue you need to cover your costs</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-400 transition-transform" data-suite-stepper-target="chevron" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
    </button>
    <div data-suite-stepper-target="panel" class="border-t border-gray-200/80 dark:border-gray-800 p-6">
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">Start by understanding your break-even point -- the amount of sales you need to cover all fixed and variable costs before you start making a profit.</p>
      <%= link_to "Open Break-Even Calculator", finance_break_even_path, class: "inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-2.5 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-600 to-orange-600 text-white rounded-xl hover:from-amber-700 hover:to-orange-700 transition-all text-sm font-medium", data: { turbo_frame: "_top" } %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <%# Step 2: Business Loan %>
  <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-2xl border border-gray-200/80 dark:border-gray-800 overflow-hidden">
    <button data-action="click->suite-stepper#toggle" class="w-full flex items-center justify-between p-6 text-left group">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
        <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-500 to-orange-600 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold text-lg">2</div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white group-hover:text-amber-600 dark:group-hover:text-amber-400 transition-colors">Plan Your Financing</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-1">Calculate business loan payments and total borrowing costs</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-400 transition-transform" data-suite-stepper-target="chevron" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
    </button>
    <div data-suite-stepper-target="panel" class="hidden border-t border-gray-200/80 dark:border-gray-800 p-6">
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">If your startup costs exceed your available capital, calculate monthly loan payments and total interest to understand the true cost of borrowing.</p>
      <%= link_to "Open Business Loan Calculator", finance_business_loan_path, class: "inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-2.5 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-600 to-orange-600 text-white rounded-xl hover:from-amber-700 hover:to-orange-700 transition-all text-sm font-medium", data: { turbo_frame: "_top" } %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <%# Step 3: ROI %>
  <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-2xl border border-gray-200/80 dark:border-gray-800 overflow-hidden">
    <button data-action="click->suite-stepper#toggle" class="w-full flex items-center justify-between p-6 text-left group">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
        <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-500 to-orange-600 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold text-lg">3</div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white group-hover:text-amber-600 dark:group-hover:text-amber-400 transition-colors">Project Your ROI</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-1">Estimate the return on your total business investment</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-400 transition-transform" data-suite-stepper-target="chevron" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
    </button>
    <div data-suite-stepper-target="panel" class="hidden border-t border-gray-200/80 dark:border-gray-800 p-6">
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">With your costs and financing figured out, calculate the expected return on investment to see if the business opportunity is worth pursuing.</p>
      <%= link_to "Open ROI Calculator", finance_roi_path, class: "inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-2.5 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-600 to-orange-600 text-white rounded-xl hover:from-amber-700 hover:to-orange-700 transition-all text-sm font-medium", data: { turbo_frame: "_top" } %>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<%= render "shared/ad_slot", slot: "in_content" %>

<article class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none mt-12">
  <h2>How to Use the Business Startup Calculator Suite</h2>
  <p>Launching a business without understanding your numbers is one of the biggest reasons startups fail. This suite walks you through the critical financial calculations every entrepreneur needs before investing time and money.</p>

  <h3>Step-by-Step Guide</h3>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Break-even analysis</strong> -- Determine how many units you need to sell or how much revenue you need to cover all your costs.</li>
    <li><strong>Plan financing</strong> -- If you need a loan, calculate monthly payments and total interest so you can factor borrowing costs into your plan.</li>
    <li><strong>Project ROI</strong> -- Estimate your return on investment to make sure the business is worth pursuing compared to other uses of your capital.</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Why Start with Break-Even?</h3>
  <p>Break-even analysis is the foundation of business planning because it answers the most basic question: can this business cover its costs? Before worrying about loans or returns, you need to know whether your pricing and expected sales volume can sustain the operation. If the break-even point seems unreachable, it is better to adjust your business model before investing further.</p>

  <h3>Making Smart Financing Decisions</h3>
  <p>Not every business needs a loan. If your break-even analysis shows that you can reach profitability with your existing savings, you may be able to bootstrap. However, if you do need external funding, the Business Loan Calculator helps you compare different loan amounts, terms, and interest rates so you can choose the option that balances affordable monthly payments with reasonable total interest costs.</p>
</article>

<%= render "shared/ad_slot", slot: "multiplex" %>
